@councillors, two treasury proposals can be rejected based on the following info:

- [motion 137](https://kusama.polkassembly.io/treasury/137) is a proposal submitted mistakenly by Mr Excel. They have already submitted a corrected version of the proposal that was voted as [motion 445](https://kusama.polkassembly.io/motion/445) and already approved by Council a few weeks ago. The reason of the incorrect proposal is the use of extrinsics and the allocation unit measure in the extrinsics tab.

- [motion 141](https://kusama.polkassembly.io/treasury/141) is a proposal submitted by a UX developer studying the treasury submission process to work on some changes. This can be rejected with no issues.

Based on the feedback received from various teams and on [this discussion post](https://kusama.polkassembly.io/post/1351), motion 438 aims to vote an amended version of the call design. The changes are:

- We leave what is scheduled in LP20 for LP21 (currently on dispatch queue with Id: **Auctlp21**);
- We delete the replacement on the proposed design above for the batch Id Auctlp21: since we are leaving the original one;
- We delete the 2 extra calls on LP21 for LP21: leaving 5 auctions for LP21 instead of 8. The reasoning behind this is a. teams that need to renew will be able to do so, b. renewals are not needed on every upcoming LP, c. allow projects to catch up on development. 

The amended call design will schedule (besides what is already scheduled for LP21 on LP20):

- 6 auctions on LP21 for LP22
- 6 auctions on LP22 for LP23
- 5 auctions on LP23: 2 for LP23 and 3 for LP24
- 6 auctions on LP24: 3 for LP24 and 3 for LP25
- 6 auctions on LP25: 3 for LP25 and 3 for LP26
- 3 auctions for LP26, to onboard on LP26

All of these will be scheduled until the first days of January 2023. 

